1
00:00:12,596 --> 00:00:15,091
<i>The harder the hit,
the more it'll sting.</i>

2
00:00:15,115 --> 00:00:17,059
<i>That's usually the case.</i>

3
00:00:17,083 --> 00:00:18,928
<i>So we prescribe.</i>

4
00:00:18,952 --> 00:00:22,921
<i>Meds, ice,
compression, elevation.</i>

5
00:00:24,141 --> 00:00:26,225
<i>Things you do to stop
the immediate pain.</i>

6
00:00:27,828 --> 00:00:29,322
You left early this morning.

7
00:00:29,346 --> 00:00:31,357
Yeah, 'cause I love
it here so much.

8
00:00:31,381 --> 00:00:33,259
I had to open,
plus it looks good.

9
00:00:33,283 --> 00:00:35,078
- Is that what the lawyer said?
- Supposed to establish that

10
00:00:35,102 --> 00:00:36,896
I'm a valuable member
of the community.

11
00:00:36,920 --> 00:00:39,566
You know, to counteract the
fact that I ruined DeLuca's face.

12
00:00:39,590 --> 00:00:41,751
I meet with them
today. Strategy session.

13
00:00:41,775 --> 00:00:44,203
They say it's make or
break, whatever that means.

14
00:00:44,227 --> 00:00:46,356
<i>But you can only dull
the pain for so long,</i>

15
00:00:46,380 --> 00:00:48,547
<i>and when the drugs
start to wear off...</i>

16
00:00:50,200 --> 00:00:51,661
<i>it really hurts.</i>

17
00:00:51,685 --> 00:00:53,296
Thank you for offering to help.

18
00:00:53,320 --> 00:00:55,381
I love you, and I feel for you.

19
00:00:55,405 --> 00:00:58,990
Solidarity and all of
that, but this is scut.

20
00:01:00,477 --> 00:01:02,405
Don't think for one
second you're getting points

21
00:01:02,429 --> 00:01:03,840
for arriving before me.

22
00:01:03,864 --> 00:01:05,275
Things you didn't
do yesterday...

23
00:01:05,299 --> 00:01:06,893
refill the glove dispenser,

24
00:01:06,917 --> 00:01:08,678
check the auxiliary
thermometer batteries,

25
00:01:08,702 --> 00:01:10,519
- stock oral swabs.
- I'm out.

26
00:01:10,854 --> 00:01:12,432
And what, you think
this is a place to...

27
00:01:12,456 --> 00:01:14,167
to hang out with your friends?

28
00:01:14,191 --> 00:01:15,969
You do realize we open in
20, so you gonna sit there

29
00:01:15,993 --> 00:01:18,555
and admire me, or do
you want to get to work?

30
00:01:22,900 --> 00:01:25,181
It's a big thing for
me not to know.

31
00:01:25,719 --> 00:01:27,130
What is? Which one?

32
00:01:27,154 --> 00:01:29,666
The church one...
that you go to church.

33
00:01:29,690 --> 00:01:31,956
You go to AA.
That's a lot of praying.

34
00:01:32,793 --> 00:01:34,120
What are we gonna
tell the children

35
00:01:34,144 --> 00:01:36,172
about God and
the afterlife or...

36
00:01:36,196 --> 00:01:37,596
Wait, the children?

37
00:01:38,465 --> 00:01:40,259
- What children?
- Our children.

38
00:01:40,283 --> 00:01:41,728
So we're having children now?

39
00:01:41,752 --> 00:01:44,619
No! How can we have
children? I barely know you.

40
00:01:50,461 --> 00:01:52,341
You know, I had a thought.

41
00:01:53,247 --> 00:01:55,547
You and I should...

42
00:01:56,549 --> 00:01:58,178
hang out together.

43
00:01:58,202 --> 00:01:59,562
You know, somewhere
that isn't here.

44
00:01:59,586 --> 00:02:01,085
Like, uh...

45
00:02:02,389 --> 00:02:04,050
- A movie?
- No.

46
00:02:04,074 --> 00:02:06,091
Maybe I could
just show up there,

47
00:02:06,493 --> 00:02:07,804
and then you show up,

48
00:02:07,828 --> 00:02:09,990
and hey, look,
we're hanging out.

49
00:02:10,014 --> 00:02:11,246
I don't hang out.

50
00:02:11,865 --> 00:02:12,865
You could.

51
00:02:14,484 --> 00:02:16,096
Come on. We're in the clear.

52
00:02:16,120 --> 00:02:18,486
Pierce asked me out.
I let her down gently.

53
00:02:20,373 --> 00:02:21,267
We could try.

54
00:02:21,291 --> 00:02:22,468
There's no trying.

55
00:02:22,492 --> 00:02:25,293
We are not that type of friends.

56
00:02:26,196 --> 00:02:28,597
All right, well, what
type of friends are we?

57
00:02:29,967 --> 00:02:31,199
I'm leaving.

58
00:02:37,158 --> 00:02:38,257
It's progress.

59
00:02:39,042 --> 00:02:41,562
Sorry I'm late. What do we have?

60
00:02:42,028 --> 00:02:43,345
Jackson...

61
00:02:51,921 --> 00:02:53,641
- Dr. Avery!
- Yeah, I'll get her.

62
00:02:54,258 --> 00:02:55,351
- Hey.
- Hey.

63
00:02:55,375 --> 00:02:57,287
Just, um, catching up.

64
00:02:57,311 --> 00:02:58,505
Tough night with Harriet?

65
00:02:58,529 --> 00:03:00,490
She got up like six times.

66
00:03:00,514 --> 00:03:01,841
- Or maybe seven.
- Ohh.

67
00:03:03,150 --> 00:03:06,011
Does it count if she wakes just
as we're putting her back down?

68
00:03:06,035 --> 00:03:08,548
"We"? What, you and April?

69
00:03:08,572 --> 00:03:10,667
No, you guys... You have
to switch off, take turns.

70
00:03:10,691 --> 00:03:12,034
Yeah, I know. We are, totally.

71
00:03:12,058 --> 00:03:13,653
I mean, kind of.

72
00:03:13,677 --> 00:03:15,372
It's just, you know, she's
recovering from surgery,

73
00:03:15,396 --> 00:03:17,707
so every time it's
her turn, I still get up

74
00:03:17,731 --> 00:03:20,160
and see how she's doing,
which makes her feel guilty,

75
00:03:20,184 --> 00:03:22,712
so then she tries to come
and help when it's my turn,

76
00:03:22,736 --> 00:03:24,631
and I spend that entire
time trying to convince her

77
00:03:24,655 --> 00:03:28,167
that she needs to get
rested up for... for her turn.

78
00:03:28,191 --> 00:03:29,586
Which you then get up for, too.

79
00:03:29,610 --> 00:03:31,437
It's not a perfect system.

80
00:03:31,461 --> 00:03:33,623
But, I'm ready to
work, you know?

81
00:03:33,647 --> 00:03:35,341
I'm just... I'm cranking
away right here.

82
00:03:35,365 --> 00:03:37,611
Yeah, well, um, tell you
what. I'll take point on rounds

83
00:03:37,635 --> 00:03:39,996
by way of the
coffee cart, and...

84
00:03:41,655 --> 00:03:44,668
Or not. Got a trauma
on the helipad.

85
00:03:44,692 --> 00:03:46,874
- You're on your own.
- Yeah, a couple minutes.

86
00:03:49,146 --> 00:03:50,723
Hold that elevator.

87
00:03:50,747 --> 00:03:52,430
Yep. Hey.

88
00:03:53,800 --> 00:03:55,117
You look tired.

89
00:03:55,836 --> 00:03:58,764
Well, I've been up a while
with Amelia talking and talking.

90
00:03:58,788 --> 00:04:01,267
She's yours now. I'm
not taking her back.

91
00:04:01,291 --> 00:04:03,553
I'm good. She's great.
We're... We're great.

92
00:04:05,145 --> 00:04:07,140
You have the rest of
this elevator ride. Go.

93
00:04:07,164 --> 00:04:09,192
You know, she gets
an idea into her head

94
00:04:09,216 --> 00:04:10,343
and she just won't let it go.

95
00:04:10,367 --> 00:04:12,162
She's relentless,
like a... like a shark.

96
00:04:12,186 --> 00:04:14,014
- She just won't put it down.
- Two more floors.

97
00:04:14,038 --> 00:04:15,614
And she asks me a
question and I answer it,

98
00:04:15,638 --> 00:04:17,166
and my answer just
causes more questions,

99
00:04:17,190 --> 00:04:20,320
and suddenly I've forgotten
what we're talking about

100
00:04:20,344 --> 00:04:21,424
and I'm late for work.

101
00:04:21,578 --> 00:04:23,239
And I love her,
and it's exhausting.

102
00:04:23,263 --> 00:04:24,943
- Do you feel better?
- Yeah, a little bit.

103
00:04:26,900 --> 00:04:28,378
Glider plane crashed
near Snoqualmie Falls.

104
00:04:28,402 --> 00:04:30,330
Two passengers, both
conscious at the scene.

105
00:04:30,354 --> 00:04:32,431
Is Polly behind
me? She's my wife.

106
00:04:32,455 --> 00:04:34,384
Is she okay? I need
to see her. Please.

107
00:04:34,408 --> 00:04:36,819
Polly Campbell, 33,
B.P.'s 90 over 40.

108
00:04:36,843 --> 00:04:38,704
Blunt trauma to the
chest and abdomen.

109
00:04:38,728 --> 00:04:40,040
Where's Daniel? Is he okay?

110
00:04:40,064 --> 00:04:41,344
We've got him.

111
00:04:46,536 --> 00:04:48,931
Timir, uh, I wanted
to ask a favor.

112
00:04:48,955 --> 00:04:51,017
Look, I need to leave for
about an hour this afternoon,

113
00:04:51,041 --> 00:04:52,568
but I can be back before close.

114
00:04:52,592 --> 00:04:54,921
I know you consider
this grunt work, Dr. Karev.

115
00:04:54,945 --> 00:04:57,307
It's a far cry from the hallowed
halls of the surgical floor.

116
00:04:57,331 --> 00:04:58,641
I didn't say that.

117
00:04:58,665 --> 00:05:00,810
And I'm sure you're not used
to taking orders from a nurse.

118
00:05:00,834 --> 00:05:03,513
- No, it's fine. I just...
- Oh, is it fine?

119
00:05:03,537 --> 00:05:04,564
Thank you.

120
00:05:04,588 --> 00:05:06,899
This is second Thursday.
Vaccination day.

121
00:05:06,923 --> 00:05:08,567
We're about to get flooded
by hundreds of patients

122
00:05:08,591 --> 00:05:09,919
needing shots on
top of everyone else.

123
00:05:09,943 --> 00:05:11,570
I wouldn't ask if it
wasn't important.

124
00:05:11,594 --> 00:05:13,706
What's important
is our patients.

125
00:05:13,730 --> 00:05:16,197
They can't be rescheduled
like elective surgeries.

126
00:05:16,883 --> 00:05:19,195
They need you here and
so do I. The answer's no.

127
00:05:19,219 --> 00:05:20,896
You figure out your life
on your own schedule.

128
00:05:20,920 --> 00:05:22,299
Clinic's open.

129
00:05:22,323 --> 00:05:23,323
Get the doors.

130
00:05:27,695 --> 00:05:30,239
Pierce, you see this page?
Cardio consult in the pit.

131
00:05:30,263 --> 00:05:31,441
Oh, well, if you're going...

132
00:05:31,465 --> 00:05:32,708
You want to go?
I don't have to go.

133
00:05:32,732 --> 00:05:34,326
No, you... you're already going.

134
00:05:34,350 --> 00:05:36,012
- Why would I go?
- 'Cause you were going.

135
00:05:36,036 --> 00:05:37,714
Well, I'm not,
though, if you are.

136
00:05:37,738 --> 00:05:40,065
- So I'll go.
- And I will not go.

137
00:05:40,089 --> 00:05:41,569
- Excuse me.
- Okay.

138
00:05:42,308 --> 00:05:43,308
Okay...

139
00:05:44,428 --> 00:05:45,705
- I - want to see my husband.

140
00:05:45,729 --> 00:05:47,040
Try and hold still for me.

141
00:05:47,064 --> 00:05:49,692
Is Daniel hurt? Can
you at least tell me that?

142
00:05:49,716 --> 00:05:51,310
He's in the other room
getting checked out.

143
00:05:51,334 --> 00:05:52,344
There's some fluid in the belly.

144
00:05:52,368 --> 00:05:53,896
We're gonna need a
CT. To take a better look.

145
00:05:53,920 --> 00:05:55,281
Was your husband
flying the glider?

146
00:05:55,305 --> 00:05:57,133
It was his first time up
there without an instructor,

147
00:05:57,157 --> 00:05:58,401
and he wanted me to go.

148
00:05:58,425 --> 00:06:01,287
He worked so hard for this.

149
00:06:01,311 --> 00:06:03,423
- SATs are dropping.
- She's gonna need a chest tube.

150
00:06:03,447 --> 00:06:06,860
Please, please tell
me he'll be okay.

151
00:06:06,884 --> 00:06:07,884
I got him, Polly,

152
00:06:07,951 --> 00:06:10,112
but I need to make sure
you can breathe first, okay?

153
00:06:10,136 --> 00:06:11,247
- Okay, how can I help?
- Lido.

154
00:06:11,271 --> 00:06:12,882
Twenty-eight French,
and set up a pleurovac.

155
00:06:12,906 --> 00:06:15,618
Still dropping.
SATs are down to 88.

156
00:06:15,642 --> 00:06:17,053
I've got it. Will you move?

157
00:06:18,729 --> 00:06:20,406
Polly, I'm sorry.

158
00:06:33,643 --> 00:06:35,043
There you go.

159
00:06:41,935 --> 00:06:44,497
- How is he? Superficial
facial lacerations.

160
00:06:44,521 --> 00:06:46,249
But right leg, though.

161
00:06:46,273 --> 00:06:48,752
I'm fine. Please,
go help my wife.

162
00:06:48,776 --> 00:06:50,286
She's asking for you, too.

163
00:06:50,310 --> 00:06:51,687
She's being treated
in the next room.

164
00:06:51,711 --> 00:06:53,144
I'm telling you I'm fine.

165
00:07:02,272 --> 00:07:04,867
I'm gonna need sandbags
and a spinal x-ray.

166
00:07:04,891 --> 00:07:05,935
Okay.

167
00:07:05,959 --> 00:07:07,086
I just want to see Polly.

168
00:07:07,110 --> 00:07:09,188
Daniel, I'm gonna need
to get a spinal x-ray.

169
00:07:09,212 --> 00:07:11,991
- I can't feel my legs.
- Okay, I don't want you
to be alarmed.

170
00:07:12,015 --> 00:07:14,544
No, I mean I haven't
felt them for three years.

171
00:07:14,568 --> 00:07:16,062
I'm paraplegic.

172
00:07:16,086 --> 00:07:18,236
Oh. Well, okay.

173
00:07:18,638 --> 00:07:20,650
Where's Daniel?
I want to see him!

174
00:07:20,674 --> 00:07:21,701
Daniel!

175
00:07:21,725 --> 00:07:24,053
- Owen, stop.
- Sweetie, you there?

176
00:07:24,077 --> 00:07:25,121
Daniel?

177
00:07:25,145 --> 00:07:26,706
I'm here! Are you okay?

178
00:07:26,730 --> 00:07:28,407
- Are you all right?
- Are you okay?

179
00:07:28,431 --> 00:07:29,992
- I'm all right.
- I'm okay, I think.

180
00:07:30,016 --> 00:07:32,467
Polly, I wish I could see you.

181
00:07:33,153 --> 00:07:35,436
- I love you so much.
- I love you, too.

182
00:07:35,956 --> 00:07:37,706
Polly, I'm so sorry!

183
00:07:38,808 --> 00:07:40,836
Polly?

184
00:07:40,860 --> 00:07:42,494
I noticed it a couple weeks ago.

185
00:07:42,913 --> 00:07:45,107
Now it smells kind of funny.

186
00:07:45,131 --> 00:07:46,809
That is one infected abscess.

187
00:07:46,833 --> 00:07:48,993
We're gonna have
to open that up.

188
00:07:50,370 --> 00:07:51,664
What are you doing?

189
00:07:51,688 --> 00:07:53,783
My patient needs an
I&D for his abscess.

190
00:07:53,807 --> 00:07:55,751
Yeah, not by you. Page surgery.

191
00:07:55,775 --> 00:07:57,219
I am surgery.

192
00:07:57,243 --> 00:07:58,871
Not in here you're
not. You do not lance,

193
00:07:58,895 --> 00:08:00,856
you do not drain,
you do not cut.

194
00:08:00,880 --> 00:08:02,024
It'll take five minutes.

195
00:08:02,048 --> 00:08:04,360
You are not authorized to
use a scalpel on anyone.

196
00:08:04,384 --> 00:08:05,700
Page surgery.

197
00:08:07,170 --> 00:08:08,787
I thought you said
you were a surgeon.

198
00:08:24,737 --> 00:08:26,165
I wanted to let you know

199
00:08:26,189 --> 00:08:29,385
that the internal reports
have been completed and filed.

200
00:08:29,409 --> 00:08:30,903
Copies will be mailed to you,

201
00:08:30,927 --> 00:08:33,272
and all your records
have gone to the D.A.

202
00:08:33,296 --> 00:08:34,474
Okay. Thanks.

203
00:08:34,498 --> 00:08:36,325
Uh, one more thing.

204
00:08:36,349 --> 00:08:39,511
While the legal
proceedings are still ongoing,

205
00:08:39,535 --> 00:08:42,531
you are not to
discuss this matter

206
00:08:42,555 --> 00:08:44,166
within the walls
of this hospital.

207
00:08:44,190 --> 00:08:46,218
Don't talk about it to anyone.

208
00:08:46,242 --> 00:08:48,009
- Understood?
- Yeah, I understand.

209
00:08:49,812 --> 00:08:51,507
You know, it won't be
hard not to talk about it

210
00:08:51,531 --> 00:08:54,015
'cause no one talks to me
much now anyways, so...

211
00:08:59,873 --> 00:09:02,334
You know, Dr. Avery's being
called in as an expert, I think.

212
00:09:02,358 --> 00:09:03,753
DeLuca, what'd I just say?

213
00:09:03,777 --> 00:09:06,277
Right. Don't talk to anyone.

214
00:09:06,846 --> 00:09:08,046
Got it.

215
00:09:11,251 --> 00:09:13,134
Pan scan with contrast, please.

216
00:09:15,556 --> 00:09:17,767
How old was I when my dad died?

217
00:09:17,791 --> 00:09:18,784
Sorry?

218
00:09:18,808 --> 00:09:20,375
How old was I when my dad died?

219
00:09:20,861 --> 00:09:22,138
- Five.
- I was five.

220
00:09:22,162 --> 00:09:23,689
See, you knew that.

221
00:09:23,713 --> 00:09:28,232
But your dad died, too, and
I have no idea when or how.

222
00:09:28,852 --> 00:09:30,535
It hasn't come up.

223
00:09:31,438 --> 00:09:33,082
Well, don't you
think it should have?

224
00:09:33,106 --> 00:09:35,134
Or maybe we didn't
give it enough time to.

225
00:09:35,158 --> 00:09:37,075
We gave ourselves a
two-week engagement.

226
00:09:37,978 --> 00:09:39,171
I think we're okay.

227
00:09:39,195 --> 00:09:41,374
I think I should know how old
you were when your father died.

228
00:09:41,398 --> 00:09:42,908
- It's...
- Almost 10.

229
00:09:44,034 --> 00:09:45,261
He knows?

230
00:09:48,338 --> 00:09:49,338
Hey, sorry.

231
00:09:50,790 --> 00:09:52,869
- What? It's not
a secret, is it?
- No.

232
00:09:52,893 --> 00:09:54,203
- Was that a secret?
- No, no.

233
00:09:54,227 --> 00:09:56,272
It's just she's
worried about stuff

234
00:09:56,296 --> 00:09:58,941
she doesn't need
to be worried about.

235
00:09:58,965 --> 00:10:01,694
Makes it a little more difficult
than it needs to be, right?

236
00:10:01,718 --> 00:10:03,195
Yeah, it's worth it, though.

237
00:10:03,219 --> 00:10:05,253
Definitely.

238
00:10:09,325 --> 00:10:10,403
Scans up?

239
00:10:10,427 --> 00:10:11,893
Nope. Just started.

240
00:10:15,882 --> 00:10:18,327
You're back. I didn't
know you were here.

241
00:10:18,351 --> 00:10:20,496
No, I'm not back.

242
00:10:20,520 --> 00:10:24,889
I'm here early for my
appointment with Dr. Robbins.

243
00:10:25,324 --> 00:10:26,619
Six hours early.

244
00:10:26,643 --> 00:10:29,722
Baby's in the nursery,
so I'm here to finally sleep.

245
00:10:29,746 --> 00:10:31,323
Dibs on the bottom bunk.

246
00:10:31,347 --> 00:10:34,376
Don't you have a bed
of your own at home?

247
00:10:34,400 --> 00:10:35,800
Not my home.

248
00:10:36,386 --> 00:10:39,665
I can't day-nap there
'cause it's cleaning day,

249
00:10:39,689 --> 00:10:42,852
and people are
vacuuming and polishing.

